Example: List `average`
-----------------------

\begin{code}
{-@ average :: [Int] -> Int @-}
average xs  = total `div` n
  where
    total   = foldr (+) 0 xs
    n       = length xs

length        :: [a] -> Int
length []     = 0
length (_:xs) = 1 + length xs
\end{code}

Yikes! `average` requires **non-empty** lists!

